<paragraph id="4803A6974D1D8A1B4BE8939701A63C63" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Flowering year round [?], although no collections made in February, May, and September.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="95EDC3F5A4D670FEC30F2C5E20DB8681" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="713C3304FE4868D1A6CD3B94A2EB5FB1" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="50BC20EBD60CFF2434E3110D14393BC2" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName id="38FA9516B3D60E698A3E4C22FB0263C8" authorityName="Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa hitchcockiana" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hitchcockiana">
<emphasis id="FAD38F03D7DB565514274FA0537E466E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa hitchcockiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found along the paramo or moist jalca vegetation between 2000-4025 m of the Cordillera de los Andes in Colombia, Ecuador, Bolivia, and Peru.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66B8D014AA641FF8F239A964672AFDE9" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="E211618ABA7224C7CB7C0EC65C60024E" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D42EAA41238CBE3392D0E33898E270EA" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Since the species is widespread it is of least concern (
<bibRefCitation id="A9AC6C53A13FE377DE85D92A045D13D6" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="US Department of Agriculture Miscellaneous Publication" pageId="11" pageNumber="118" refId="B13" refString="IUCN, 2010. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2010.3." title="IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2010.3" year="2010">IUCN 2010</bibRefCitation>
). However, the typical size of populations is undocumented and it has been noted by the authors that the grass is sought after by grazers since it is often found growing among the protection of perennial shrubs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25AC27363FD7D2EAF1CE7A976450D1F5" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1D256C81B1FD5F0CEBEB8632492CE10A" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB3B28C08A88DCEB6AD92F27B21FEFA4" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Since the epithets 
<emphasis id="D5EDA10BECE7E847D2A83D04E6D3BC5D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">procumbens</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="22226C083578F1E34D9D9430C7DEE316" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">decumbens</emphasis>
are blocked in 
<taxonomicName id="33770D5FCF86B0D5666A0C6E7C91E3E2" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CE1C4AC7E5270946AF65614C4D025554" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the earlier 
<taxonomicName id="41CBF8D4C1AE00EE89B6C3CD19ADDDD8" authorityName="Curtis" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa procumbens" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis id="4E78923CAA3ED5C13C32634AF0B3CFCA" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Curtis and 
<taxonomicName id="8DCEFE82F36AC734E85731E2FDC3DF6D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa decumbens" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decumbens">
<emphasis id="D35CF0D015E8A2AA90541422A296D0B5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa decumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Scop., we provide a new name commemorating the &quot;father of American agrostology,&quot; Albert Spear Hitchcock (1865-1935).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EC89401DA4D64443CEF11A7F77FC958F" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="comments">
<paragraph id="041059D6004633A0C2719DC09E0959FD" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A5067F97CD29748FF042433C694948E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
The only wide ranging species of 
<taxonomicName id="E7C5892DE08BA967F446BE888AC9A607" authority="subsect. Aphanelytrum" authorityName="subsect. Aphanelytrum (Hack.) Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="subsect. Tovarochloa (Macfarl. &amp; P. But) Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" subsection="Aphanelytrum">Poa subsect. Aphanelytrum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0D18432E022B88ACCC7D18C52E2EDDB1" authorityName="Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa hitchcockiana" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hitchcockiana">
<emphasis id="93762038CBFE9CFE78FD4F42C374BC97" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa hitchcockiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the most unusual spikelet morphology with extremely long rachillas (1.5-4.2 mm long) and very short [0.1-0.5 (-0.7) mm long] to obscure or often absent, unveined glumes. 
<taxonomicName id="E273B75290D3E6A26A08F4D1658DA092" authorityName="subsect. Aphanelytrum (Hack.) Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="subsect. Tovarochloa (Macfarl. &amp; P. But) Soreng &amp; P. M. Peterson" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2EB57DF23E31EAEDAB5205F45297F63C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rachillas rarely exceed 1.5 mm, but some have spikelets with rachillas up to 2 mm long (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="0DA41333A8732E1B6EFD404908BC413B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="sect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Secundae">Poa sect. Secundae</taxonomicName>
V.L. Marsh ex Soreng) 
<taxonomicName id="87A9D87DAA1DF9DA366257C3D064AF2F" authorityName="Scribn" authorityYear="1899" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa curtifolia" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="curtifolia">
<emphasis id="11CD481EC96D85F67EEE9CF25032D629" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa curtifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scribn., 
<taxonomicName id="6AF32F3E01FB91021DD080A2C829C902" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa hartzii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hartzii">
<emphasis id="355624DD8135E03BABA9F243CE23EA58" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa hartzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gand., 
<taxonomicName id="98C14D96668A83651CD30BDEB5A0B89F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa stenantha" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stenantha">
<emphasis id="4CFA51B09F39A5BC68DE6BB2456A20E8" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Poa stenantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Trin.; (
<taxonomicName id="511C40A729083CE75608049124534FAD" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="sect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Cenisiae">Poa sect. Cenisiae</taxonomicName>
<pageBreakToken id="6F4A2E04455E49EAAE229332A37E294B" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" start="start">Asch</pageBreakToken>
. &amp; Graebn.) 
<taxonomicName id="8806D9966339F6502CC8B68B464FC9B5" authorityName="Bor" authorityYear="1972" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa davisii" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davisii">
<emphasis id="D75E6E9AAB6365FBFFA2B573B7170E1A" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Poa davisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bor; (
<taxonomicName id="FC03AB10C669A390EE66D568B8881797" authority="supersect. Homalopoa" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="supersect." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" supersection="Homalopoa">Poa supersect. Homalopoa</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="C3CC4608824F9886DEDFA995C07340E6" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa bajaensis" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bajaensis">
<emphasis id="7F6AB3280DCF8DA3D60B81CEF34C896B" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Poa bajaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Soreng, and a few other species in the 
<taxonomicName id="761967FFB255D65AB798B05B24E5BB39" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Homalopoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Homalopoa" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="468AAA3DBB5066251014A95FF085D202" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Homalopoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(H) clade (see 
<bibRefCitation id="293CDEAEFC0B5ABC6CFC1F05566D208A" author="Soreng, RJ" editor="Seberg, O" journalOrPublisher="Aarhus University Press, Aarhus" pageId="11" pageNumber="118" pagination="619 - 644" refId="B27" refString="Soreng, RJ, Bull, RD, Gillespie, LJ, 2010. Phylogeny and reticulation in Poa based on plastid trnTLF and nrITS sequences with attention to diploids. In: Seberg, O, Petersen, G, Barfod, AS, Davis, JI, Eds., Diversity, Phylogeny, and Evolution in the Monocotyledons. Aarhus University Press, Aarhus: 619 - 644" title="Phylogeny and reticulation in Poa based on plastid trnTLF and nrITS sequences with attention to diploids." volumeTitle="Diversity, Phylogeny, and Evolution in the Monocotyledons." year="2010">Soreng et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Four species of the related genus 
<taxonomicName id="5DB7C8538FFFA52D79BC163B17407A1A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nicoraepoa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nicoraepoa" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="922E3AF89C304D843EB8234BAB49D3DE" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Nicoraepoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Soreng &amp; L.J. Gillespie have rachillas up to 3 mm long (
<bibRefCitation id="4CFAAB543EE31CB1E1B0AA2717D2AFF1" author="Soreng, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="11" pageNumber="118" pagination="821 - 849" refId="B29" refString="Soreng, RJ, Gillespie, LJ, 2007. Nicoraepoa (Poaceae, Poeae), a new South American genus based on Poa subgenus Andinae, and emendation of Poa section Parodiochloa of the sub-Antarctic islands. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 94: 821 - 849" title="Nicoraepoa (Poaceae, Poeae), a new South American genus based on Poa subgenus Andinae, and emendation of Poa section Parodiochloa of the sub-Antarctic islands." volume="94" year="2007">Soreng and Gillespie 2007</bibRefCitation>
). However, there are no known species of 
<taxonomicName id="F787E27A47C513C7D0147375C52C6E8F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7204515896A2A83608A0ACC6C73847B8" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with unveined glumes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
